<h1>Heterodox economics</h1>

<figure>
<img src="00.jpg"/>
</figure>

<p>
Heterodox economics refers to methodologies or schools of economic thought that are considered outside of "mainstream economics", often represented by expositors as contrasting with or going beyond neoclassical economics.
</p>

